Example 2 — "why is the checkout pod crashing?":
1. kubectl get pods (find the exact pod name matching checkout)
2. kubectl describe pod <pod> (use the exact name from step 1; check Events at the bottom)
3. kubectl logs --previous --tail=200 <pod>
4. Report the crash reason from events plus the last error lines from the logs.

Example 3 — "scale the api deployment to 5 replicas in namespace prod-ns" (guarded mutation):
1. kubectl config current-context (confirm and report the context; if it looks like production and the user did not name it, stop and ask)
2. kubectl get deployments -n prod-ns (confirm a deployment named api exists; if not, stop and ask)
3. kubectl scale deployment/api --replicas=5 -n prod-ns
4. kubectl get deployments -n prod-ns (verify READY shows 5/5 or report progress)
5. Report the context, namespace, deployment, and new replica count.
